    A sub-interface that allows implementations to throw checked exceptions.

    Interface for binary predicates that derive their result from two input values.

    A sub-interface that allows implementations to throw checked exceptions.
    ElementAccess<E>
    An interface for objects that implement access to certain elements of other objects.

    A combined interface for functions that access certain elements in objects.

    Interface for functions that return a value that will be derived from an input value.

    An extended function interface for invertible functions.

    Interface for predicate functions that return a boolean value that is derived from a target object.
